    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the annual salary of all public sector workers by 3%.",
        "additional_details": "\"The starting salary for Police Officers in England, Wales and Northern Ireland is between \u00a319,971 and \u00a323,124, rising to \u00a338,382 at the top of the scale - achievable after about seven years..\"\r\n\r\n\"Public Sector workers help you when you need it, no matter how bad of a situation. Some make you feel safe and risk their whole life for us, saving lives. They train and dedicated their life to make sure the people of Britain are safe and secure in the area that they live. They deserve more.\" - Nameless",
        "background": "We, the people of Britain, would like to request an increase of the annual salary for all public sector workers by 3%. In particular, the pay wage of Police, Firefighters and workers of the NHS. \r\n\r\nWe feel that the wages should be increased because of the heroic services they provide everyday.",
